        "comment": "The snow cover is mostly wet due to the warming and typical spring weather, only slightly frozen in the morning. The air temperature reaches positive (+) values in all altitudes of the Tatras. Continuous snow cover occurs only at high altitudes, on the northern slopes and in the middle altitudes from about 1300 to 1600 m above sea level.  Its height reaches 50 to 150 cm, the most snow at a comparable height is in the Low Tatras."
